switch to blog "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==============================================================

NAME
----

switch to blog - Switch the current blog to a different blog. **switch\_to\_blog()**, is

SYNOPSIS
--------

Switch the current blog to a different blog. **switch\_to\_blog()**, is
useful if you need to pull posts or other information from other blogs.

You can switch back afterwards using
[restore\_current\_blog()](/Function_Reference/restore_current_blog "Function Reference/restore current blog").

Things that aren't switched:

-   autoloaded options. See
    \#[14992](http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/14992 "http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/14992")
-   plugins. See
    \#[14941](http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/14941 "http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/14941")
-   [the object
    cache](http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/14992 "http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/14992")

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$new_blog` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The id of the blog you want to switch to.
    Default: current blog

 `$validate` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to check if \$new\_blog exists before
    proceeding
    Default: false

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(bool)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   true on success, false if the validation failed

`false` if `$validate=true` is passed and no such blog exists; otherwise
`true` (even when "switching" to the current blog).

SOURCE FILE
-----------

switch\_to\_blog() is located in `wp-includes/ms-blogs.php`

You can switch back afterwards using restore\_current\_blog()

